external_knowledge:
Older brands refer to those where the products haven't had a stock check or quality control review in over a year.;
The term "average quality scores" refers to the arithmetic mean of all quality scores for the products within each brand.;
"Product count" refers to the total number of products linked to each brand in question.;

sql:
SELECT *
FROM product_movements
WHERE from_warehouse_id = 1;

SELECT product_id, web_description, size
FROM products
WHERE brand = 'Wilko' AND washable = 'yes';

SELECT web_description, dimensions
FROM products
WHERE availability = 1 AND dq_score > 8.0;

SELECT p.product_id, p.web_description, s.supplier_name
FROM products AS p
JOIN suppliers AS s ON p.supplier_id = s.supplier_id;

SELECT product_id, web_description, dq_score
FROM products
WHERE product_id = 12345;
